## How to process a Centrapay transaction

1. **Display the payment amount on the terminal.**
   Once the payment amount is confirmed, it will be displayed on the terminal.
   ![terminals with payments](/terminals/payment-amount.png)

2. **Find and Tap the Centrapay Logo**
   Locate the Centrapay payment option on the terminal screen. (usually represented by an orange Centrapay icon). Tap on it to select Centrapay as the payment method.

   On different terminals, the Centrapay logo may appear in different locations. Here are some examples of different scenarios:

   * On some devices, the Centrapay option can be seen on the first screen, displayed as either a logo or text option.
   ![terminals with payment option](/terminals/centrapay-first-page.png)

   * On some devices, you may need to scroll or check the QR payment options menu to find Centrapay.

     {% wrapper class="flex flex-wrap gap-6 justify-start not-prose" %}
      {% imageGrid
        image="/terminals/centrapay-second-page.png"
        caption="Scroll through the list of payment options to see the Centrapay logo"
        imageWidth="73"
      /%}
      {% imageGrid
        image="/terminals/qr-payments-option.png"
        caption="Click QR Payments first to see the Centrapay logo"
        imageWidth="73"
      /%}
     {% /wrapper %}

   * When Centrapay is selected, the terminal will display a unique Centrapay QR code linked to the specific payment amount. It is now ready for the customer to scan using a compatible app.
   ![terminals with payments](/terminals/qr-codes.png)

3. **Scan the Centrapay QR code**
   The customer opens a mobile app the supports Centrapay QR codes, such as Payap, the Farmlands App, or even the native camera. Payment availability may vary depending on the store's setup.

   They then select the \"Scan\" function and scan the Centrapay QR code displayed on the terminal screen. The app will automatically recognize and process the transaction.

    {% wrapper class="flex flex-wrap gap-6 justify-start not-prose items-center" %}
     {% imageGrid image="/terminals/terminal-with-highlighted-qr.png" /%}

      {% wrapper class="flex flex-col" %}
        {% wrapper class="font-normal text-xs mb-4" %}
          Compatible Apps for Centrapay QR Code:
        {% /wrapper %}
        {% wrapper class="flex flex-wrap gap-6 justify-start not-prose" %}
         {% imageGrid image="/appIcons/payap-app-icon.png" /%}
         {% imageGrid image="/appIcons/farmlands-app-icon.png" /%}
         {% imageGrid image="/appIcons/gift-station-app-icon.png" /%}
         {% imageGrid image="/appIcons/camera-app-icon.png" /%}
        {% /wrapper %}
      {% /wrapper %}
    {% /wrapper %}

4. **Complete the Payment**
   Once the scan is successful, the customer will confirm the payment in the app. The terminal screen will then display a transaction completion message, and both the customer and the merchant will see as successful payment notification.
   ![payap completed payment](/payap-completed-payment.png)

